                            <comment id="227530" author="standan" created="Tue, 8 May 2018 19:32:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 2.10.3&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/61129d8e-5067-11e8-abc3-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/61129d8e-5067-11e8-abc3-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="215178" author="adilger" created="Fri, 1 Dec 2017 22:30:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It isn&apos;t clear why this test is failing in interop, but the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;-ENOTSUPP&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; (&lt;tt&gt;-524&lt;/tt&gt;) error returned from &lt;tt&gt;nrs_tbf_start()&lt;/tt&gt; is not being handled for some reason.  It doesn&apos;t look like a functionality bug, just a test script bug.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It might be better to return &lt;tt&gt;-EOPNOTSUPP&lt;/tt&gt;, which is a more standard error code, since bash only allows errors &amp;lt; 256 I think.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
